Fluers
======

Fluers is a native Rust port of the architecture of Flue
(https://github.com/withastro/flue), an agent harness framework by the
Astro team, licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.

Fluers re-implements Flue's architectural concepts from first principles
in Rust. It is not a line-by-line translation of the TypeScript source:
the harness layer (`@flue/runtime`) is re-expressed as `fluers-runtime`,
and the two foundational libraries Flue depends on
(`@earendil-works/pi-agent-core` and `@earendil-works/pi-ai`, which have
no Rust equivalent) are re-implemented as `fluers-core`.

Per the Apache-2.0 license (Section 4d), derivative works must preserve
attribution. Source files that port specific behavior from a named Flue
file carry a doc comment citing the upstream path, e.g.:

    //! Mirrors Flue's `packages/runtime/src/agent.ts`.

